                  <handDesc>
                  <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                  <seg type="rubrication">
                  <foreign xml:lang="gez">ኢግዚአብሔር፡</foreign>
                  <foreign xml:lang="gez">ማርያም፡</foreign>
                  </seg>
                  <desc>The word God is rubricated in the first three works; the word Mary is rubricated in the final two works. Occasionally, God is rubricated in alternating red and black letters (e.g., <locus target="#7r #7v" facs="008 009">fols. 7r, 7v</locus>)</desc>
                  <desc>Columetric layout of text: <locus target="#115r" facs="116">fols. 115r, </locus> (Ps. 150); <locus target="#123v #124r" facs="125">123v, 124r</locus> (tenth biblical canticle)</desc>
                  </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1"><locus target="#148r" facs="149">Fol. 148r</locus><desc>Crude drawing of a figure</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d2">
                    Decorative designs:
                    <locus target="#1r #14r #21v #37v #43r #62v #70v #75v #88v #103v #109v #115v #127r" facs="002 015 023 039 044 064 072 077 090 105 111 117 128">folss. 1r, 14r, 21v, 37v, 43r, 62v, 70v, 75v, 88v, 103v, 109v, 115v, 127r, </locus> (ḥaräg);
                    <locus target="#7r #31r #51v #100v" facs="008 032 053 102">7r, 31r, 51v, 100v, </locus> (line of alternating red and black dots);
                    <locus target="#127r #134r #148r" facs="128 135 149">127r, 134r, 148r</locus> (multiple full stops)
                    </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                  <list>
                    <item xml:id="e1">
                    <locus target="#iir(ecto)" facs="002">Fol. iir(ecto)</locus>
                    <desc>
                    scrawls
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e2">
                    <desc>
                    Numbered quires: quire 2–13
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e3">
                    <locus target="#22v #28r #29r #30v" facs="024 029 030 032">Fols. 22v, 28r, 29r, 30v</locus>
                    <desc>etc., words of text are written interlinearly
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e4">
                    <locus target="#16r #26v #28r #29v #31r" facs="017 028 029 031 032">Fols. 16r, 26v, 28r, 29v, 31r</locus>
                    <desc>etc., lines of text are written interlinearly
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e5">
                    <locus target="#143r" facs="144"> f. 143r, col. 1, line 15</locus>
                    <desc>
                    lines of text are written in the upper margin with a full stop symbol marking the location where the text is to be inserted;
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e6">
                    <locus target="#7r #13v #15r #16r" facs="008 015 016 017">Fols. 7r, 13v, 15r, 16r</locus>
                    <desc>etc., erasure markings are visible
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e7">
                    <locus target="#2v #14v #15r #22r" facs="004 016 023">Fols. 2v, 14v, 15r, 22r</locus>
                    <desc>etc., text has been removed
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e8">
                    <locus target="#17v #18r #18v" facs="021 022">Fols. 17v, 18r, 18v</locus>
                    <desc>
                    The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line. Much of the problem is addressed through the selection of an appropriate aspect ratio for the codex combined with an appropriate script size. But, where the line of text is still too long, the scribe completes the line of text above the end of the line (throughout). This scribe also will reduce the font size at the end of lines to avoid having to go onto the next line (e.g., 17v, 18rv)
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                  </list>
                </additions>
